## MDX Documentation Rules

- **No duplicate page titles.** The frontmatter `title` field is automatically rendered as the page heading by fumadocs. Do not add a `# Title` heading in the body that repeats the frontmatter title -- this produces a duplicate heading on the rendered page.
- **Start body content after the frontmatter `---` closer.** The first line of body content should be a lead paragraph or a `##` section heading, never a `#` heading that matches the title.
- **Use `##` for top-level sections.** Since the page title occupies the `#` level, all content sections should use `##` or deeper.
